Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.74,0:00:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico be behind me. Say hi to everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.97,0:01:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, honey, sweetheart. You meet people who look
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.99,0:01:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar. I don't know, they look familiar? Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.16,0:01:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I get to walk through the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.63,0:01:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,on my hands, with my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.05,0:01:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you. Anybody else?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.10,0:01:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to shake his hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.90,0:01:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,From bigism to longism.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.90,0:01:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.35,0:02:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.14,0:02:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. The long arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.51,0:02:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.63,0:02:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I shake your hand? I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.63,0:02:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the old regulars. There's all the regulars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.63,0:02:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.98,0:02:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One more.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.65,0:02:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she got two.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.29,0:02:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.31,0:03:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody I'm missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.04,0:03:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so good to see you. Ah, look who's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.66,0:03:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you're looking great today. This is a fancy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.56,0:03:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,looking jacket. Hi, sweetheart. I've seen you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. Did I shake everybody's hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't. Almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.94,0:03:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to leave a little more time for questions and answers, because we always get
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.38,0:03:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of jammed up at the end of the day. So I'll lecture less in the afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.42,0:03:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but get more time. And maybe next year we'll spend more and more time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:03:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with, you know, interviews and discussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.58,0:04:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I start all the books and end all the books
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.04,0:04:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with Gloria and Excelsis Deo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.25,0:04:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If that fries you, you're reading the wrong book.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I put that on as
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.13,0:04:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a protection at the front of the book. You know, the book
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.74,0:04:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,versus falsehood. I expected a rain of complaints, and there practically has been
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.74,0:04:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,none, because the people I don't want to read it can't get past
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.74,0:04:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that page. See, I warn everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.62,0:04:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it starts and it ends with Gloria and Excelsis Deo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.62,0:04:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To thee, O Lord, we acknowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.74,0:04:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We acknowledge thee, O Lord, as sovereign.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The narcissistic ego has a difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.64,0:05:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,time acknowledging that God is sovereign and it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The human race has lamented that for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so I just thought we'd mention that. Next year
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.29,0:05:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll do six Alder Hutchers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.29,0:05:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of twelve like we did this year, or ten, whatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.64,0:05:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll spend more time with discussion, because we've
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.22,0:05:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much gone over a lot of the academic material. And in the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.76,0:05:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,intervening months, I thought we'd do something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll produce like a, what do you call those things you play in your car
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.76,0:05:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're driving? A CD? Is that it? CD?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A CD disc, you know. So I thought we'd do them every other
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,month, so you can have something at home. You don't have to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.79,0:06:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.71,0:06:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do more of those things that you can have at your own convenience
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.06,0:06:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,without having to travel and go to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,expense of all that. So we'll try that. And Robert,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.22,0:06:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the man in the wall, is building a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.22,0:06:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to have our own recording studio at home, so we'll be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.22,0:06:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I always like President Roosevelt's fireside chats, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.22,0:06:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of a fireside chat. Where you really talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, what you've been talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.22,0:06:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,On a one-to-one basis, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.61,0:06:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, how many people here are new this time? New?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.70,0:06:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, we have. Yes, okay. So we always have
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.70,0:06:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the new and the regulars. So because of the new,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.70,0:06:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I recapitulate the basics of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.80,0:07:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness research. The basic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.21,0:07:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,discovery of consciousness research is so mind-boggling
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that few are the people on the planet that can comprehend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.21,0:07:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The only criticisms we've
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.86,0:07:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ever gotten about the work were from people who were completely unable to comprehend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.86,0:07:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We never got a single complaint that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.86,0:07:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated over 200. Can you imagine that with all the books and all the videos and all the lectures?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.86,0:07:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not one single complaint could calibrate over 200, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It is mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.30,0:07:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in all of human evolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.23,0:07:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there is now the capacity to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.23,0:07:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That is so mind-boggling that very few
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.62,0:07:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,people really comprehend it. The capacity to discern
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.86,0:08:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood is mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's limited to people who are aligned with truth rather than
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.02,0:08:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood. So only people who calibrate over 200 can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.53,0:08:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology is so simple. It's a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.62,0:08:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,physiologic response, a physiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between truth and falsehood, somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,unconsciously we always know it. There are many physiologic changes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.78,0:08:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,other than the kinesiologic response. The kinesiologic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.78,0:08:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,response is just very, very handy. It's quick and handy. You know, it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,about this long once you know how to do it. There's other physiologic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.03,0:08:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,changes. In fact, Brock gave me one off the internet
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.03,0:08:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,yesterday, that your gastric motility changes when you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.03,0:08:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,lie. And they say it's even better than a lie detector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:08:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.42,0:09:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that true? I don't know where Brock escaped to, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives me these mind-boggling things and then he twists out the door before I ask him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.42,0:09:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,questions about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.54,0:09:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so there are many physiologic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.70,0:09:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,changes having to do with the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitively we understand
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.77,0:09:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that we detect that there is a difference between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.77,0:09:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The kinesiologic response is just good
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.77,0:09:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for research. There's many other reflexes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.77,0:09:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember crossing over into Northern Ireland
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time when there was war between Northern Ireland, the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.80,0:09:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Protestants and the Catholics or whatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.50,0:09:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you crossed the border, they patted you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.50,0:09:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And as they patted you down, they looked intently into your eyes and asked you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.50,0:09:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,are you carrying any weapons? Do you intend any violence?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.73,0:10:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And they watched your pupil response.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.05,0:10:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to it after I was through it, I said to one of the detectives,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.05,0:10:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,why do you ask that? I got it. The pupil response
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is immediate. The breathing changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brain electroencephalograph changes. There are a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.46,0:10:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there's endocrine changes. There's a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.90,0:10:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote about them someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.90,0:10:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Brock brought in a new one I thought you needed to know about. It affects
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.90,0:10:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your gastric motility as well. In fact, the article, the research
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.10,0:10:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,recommends that the gastric motility response is probably more reliable
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,than the traditional lie detector tests. Blood pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.16,0:10:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,perspiration, all the various things. But
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.26,0:10:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology is quick and easy and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.48,0:10:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to those people who can't understand it, you don't need to understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.58,0:11:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You just need to do it and it works. That's all it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that are very simple mystify people. Things that are complicated, everybody gets sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.61,0:11:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.05,0:11:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to bring a couple pictures from home this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.56,0:11:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, just to demonstrate. Maybe we'll do it at the next lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How quickly, intuitively, it discerns
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.56,0:11:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood, the real from the fake, the forgery from the original.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.56,0:11:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so I'll just recapitulate again how this all arose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a huge clinic back east.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.36,0:11:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The largest psychiatric practice in the United States. 2,000 outpatients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.36,0:11:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,1,000 new patients a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.36,0:11:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a staff of 50 people, covered a couple floors, all kinds of laboratories
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and diagnostic things. 10-channel grass electroencephalogram.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.58,0:11:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We did 5-hour glucose tolerance tests and we did the electroencephalogram
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.58,0:11:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,every half hour. Because so many things
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,were incurable. One of the reasons things were incurable
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.65,0:12:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the difference between academic and clinical science.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.65,0:12:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,See, clinical science deals with what is. Academic science deals with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.65,0:12:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what it thinks is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.65,0:12:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in those days, people were
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.90,0:12:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in by the droll.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.90,0:12:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they'd been everywhere in the world and hadn't been cured, otherwise they wouldn't be coming to the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.90,0:12:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we had all the difficult cases from all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.90,0:12:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd seen all the world's experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.38,0:12:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we used every holistic health. Everything that academic science
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.38,0:12:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,tended to poo-poo was unproven. But clinical science found useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.38,0:12:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because clinically, as a physician, I can remember
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.74,0:12:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at this patient in my office, and I knew what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,non-academic therapeutic method would probably bring about recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.47,0:12:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had to make a decision. Was I going to please my colleagues
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.47,0:13:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the medical establishment, or was my obligation to this patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.47,0:13:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My obligation is to God. And at the moment of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.63,0:13:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to be accountable for what I did for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.63,0:13:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to win a popularity contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.98,0:13:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, I practiced sort of non-traditional, holistic, before it was
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,fashionable, holistic medicine. And we did,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as I say, all these tests. People poo-pooed hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we did 5-hour glucose tolerance tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.62,0:13:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd give you a huge dose of glucose, and then chart your blood sugar
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.62,0:13:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,over a period of time. And, of course, you see a normal person
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.82,0:13:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who goes up like this, and comes down slowly. Well, some people have a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.82,0:13:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,hyperinsulin response. You give them sugar, and it goes up like this, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.82,0:13:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it rockets down below normal. And as it rockets down
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.82,0:13:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,below normal, they begin to shake. Some people become violent. Some people
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.82,0:13:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,become psychotic. Some people become irrational. And I told you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,about the lady during the glucose tolerance test, who tore off all her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,clothes and ran down the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.94,0:14:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,People poo-pooed hypoglycemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.94,0:14:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When her blood sugar got down to about 70,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.94,0:14:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,she got quite psychotic, and voices told her to take off her clothes, which she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.94,0:14:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And she ran down the sidewalk. And the big lab director
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with his long white coat running after her, come back, Ms. Swanson, come back, Ms. Swanson,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.14,0:14:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and the traffic all going crazy on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.14,0:14:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply stopping sugar and sweets cures a lot of illnesses. Depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and rage attacks, and recovery from addiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.81,0:14:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and alcohol, and various things. Anyway, so I was
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.81,0:14:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,open to anything that might be helpful. We checked out things like
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.81,0:14:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,cerebral allergy, which was also poo-pooed, and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.26,0:14:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,very dilute solution. You hold it on the tongue, and a very dilute solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.26,0:15:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people become psychotic and irrational right at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The most intractable, difficult case I had, a chronic paranoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And we tested him with, I remember, potato, 1 to 100,000 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the minute it was put on the tongue, he instantly became psychotic and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.12,0:15:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,delusional and potentially violent. So we put down
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.12,0:15:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in his hospital chart, do not allow potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.12,0:15:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no clinical proof, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.25,0:15:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific proof. If you're going to wait around for proof of things, you're going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.25,0:15:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,long dead, because the proof of any of the simplest things in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.25,0:15:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, took many decades. So I heard about
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.28,0:15:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology. It was another way to help people. And I think I've told this story
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.28,0:15:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,before, but I went to the lecture by John
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Diamond. He's an excellent teacher, and he wrote a couple of good books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.34,0:15:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very clear. And when I
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.38,0:15:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,saw people go weak with certain things, I just
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.38,0:16:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,saw it from a different dimension. So I saw its usefulness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.89,0:16:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in clinical science. You know, if I want to give myself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.89,0:16:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a medication, you know how I figure out the dose. I say, this was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.89,0:16:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,50 milligrams, 100 milligrams, 150, so I take 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.27,0:16:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a result, my thyroid function is normal,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.27,0:16:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,having figured out the dose of kinesiology. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.50,0:16:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.75,0:16:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw this from a different dimension, because I'd had some other staggering
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.75,0:16:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual experiences very young in life. And I saw it as a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.75,0:16:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,holistic, I saw it as a total response of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.75,0:16:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to show the staff how we could use this. So I would go
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.42,0:16:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the world and learn these various holistic techniques, and then I'd bring it home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.42,0:16:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to the clinic, staff get together, and I'd give them a lecture of what I'd learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.42,0:16:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'd all try it and see whether, you know, as long as it's harmless,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.42,0:17:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it would be helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.42,0:17:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, it made the University
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.42,0:17:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,success and failure in a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.42,0:17:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,huge number of cases. Otherwise, we wouldn't have had
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.42,0:17:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the largest psychiatric practice in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was going to show it to the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.90,0:17:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,staff. Alright, we had
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.90,0:17:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Attitude and the Healing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.90,0:17:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Center, which of course are Miracle students.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.90,0:17:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.97,0:17:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I grabbed a couple of them, and I said
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.97,0:17:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,come over here. And, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.97,0:17:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with fluorescent lights, everybody will go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.97,0:17:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take the average person, have a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.97,0:17:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and go like this, they go weak. If you hold pesticides, or we used to use sweet and low,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they go weak. All right, well, these people didn't go weak. What's the matter with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody goes weak except them. And I found they were advanced students of A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.47,0:17:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we began testing their response. So we started with some new students of A Course in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.41,0:18:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles, and we started and tested them every week, or a couple times a month anyway. We said,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the fluorescent lights, they go weak. And put something, we wouldn't even tell them what it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.43,0:18:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is. Susan and I demonstrated this a few lectures ago, pesticides made you go weak. And then we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.86,0:18:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered that at about lectures, at about less than 75 or 80, around in there, in A Course in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.50,0:18:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles, some shift of consciousness occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they could look at a fluorescent light, and they would not go weak. In other words, they've
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,gotten the concept that you're only, you're an infinite being, and you're only subject to what you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.42,0:18:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,hold in mind. You're only subject to what you hold in mind. You're not subject to out there-ness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.13,0:18:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only subject to in here-ness, a rather enormous jump in level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the basis then of the discovery. And then the calibrations all occurred later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.24,0:18:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can start with the first slide, which, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.46,0:19:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody has seen many times. But we're not going to spend a great deal of time on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.60,0:19:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a series of lectures I did do, and spent a great deal of time on it. And now they're being
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.04,0:19:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,transcribed, transcribed, a lot of time on each level. In the book that's going to be out, I guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.56,0:19:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time of the next lecture, called Transcending Levels of Consciousness, we go into each of these
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.96,0:19:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with how to. You know, what is the block at this level? What's holding you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.39,0:19:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the payoff that you're attached to? So you're not attached to grief, anger, self-pity, and all those
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.99,0:19:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,things. You think you are. Or materialism, or sexual compulsions, et cetera. You're not attached to those
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.89,0:19:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,things at all. You just think you are. You're not really attached to them. First of all, you can't be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.16,0:20:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to them, because it's all in your head, so you're not attached to them. You're attached to the thought of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.28,0:20:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the payoff you get from it. And therefore, you don't have to surrender all these things that are so
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.58,0:20:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to surrender. You only have to surrender one thing, and that's the willingness to let go of the payoff that you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.06,0:20:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,get out of it. You've got to let go of the payoff. The willingness. So there's only one thing we're addicted to, and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.37,0:20:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the payoff that the ego gains out of misery, self-pity, being righteous, wrath, how I've been
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,cheated by life. Just because you're stupid and ugly doesn't mean you've been cheated by life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.83,0:20:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Short, stupid, and stupid. Short and ugly, that's an easy one. Where's Niko? Now stand up, Niko. Look, I love this t-shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.15,0:21:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this t-shirt. There's a man who was short and ugly, Socrates. One of the greatest names in history, and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.23,0:21:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,renowned for being bad looking. But I just thought, that's the greatest name in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.75,0:21:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Greatest t-shirt. It just knocked me out when I got here this morning. Quotes from Socrates on the back and Socrates on the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so instead of indulging in self-pity, Socrates really changed the lives of many people. And through Socratic
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.30,0:21:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding is the quickest way to forgiveness. So people who are hung up on anger and resentment and all, or guilt, all those
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.57,0:21:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,depend on forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.59,0:21:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the course of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.79,0:21:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,miracles addresses forgiveness. The 12 step groups address it. But I think the key to it is Socrates' statement, that all men can only
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.98,0:21:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,choose the good. All men choose only what they perceive to be the good. And that reveals the innate innocence within
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself. How can you forgive people? Because intrinsically, they are innocent. Intrinsically, they can't discern
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.39,0:22:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,perception from essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.27,0:22:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsically, this seems to be the good. So if blowing up people is the greatest good, then you can be sure they're going to be out there blowing up people. And of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.14,0:22:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Blowing up people, because that's where you make God happy, I guess. Okay. All right. Anyway, that's out of the naivete, the intrinsic innocence. Because the human mind by its very design is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.59,0:22:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to discern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.83,0:22:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.55,0:22:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood. The human mind is unable to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.35,0:22:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It can go with likelihood. It can go with facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.29,0:22:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with facts is nobody knows what they mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.37,0:23:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the facts. It's discerning how to assemble them and derive a meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.12,0:23:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And facts, even then, you don't have truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.54,0:23:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because truth is a different dimension than facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.60,0:23:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Facts have nothing to do with truth. Facts are just little bits of info.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.56,0:23:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Little bits of info. Now you put them together and you extract some kind of a meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.32,0:23:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have to extract significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.86,0:23:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So even though you start within the linear domain, you quickly jump to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.54,0:23:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because meaning, significance, value, and truth are abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.04,0:23:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot measure them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.34,0:23:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the cynic really...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.50,0:23:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,...really can't understand truth because they operate from lower mind, which is concrete and literal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.60,0:23:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get the facts right, but then totally miss what they mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.79,0:24:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only quizzical emails we get are from people who cannot see the forest for the trees, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.87,0:24:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They tend to get literal and concrete.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.49,0:24:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And thereby miss the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.99,0:24:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So the purpose of kinesiology is not to prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.83,0:24:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.07,0:24:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not to base anything I say on kinesiology at all, other than what the numbers come up with when you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.18,0:24:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth from which I'm speaking stands on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.08,0:24:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It stems from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.94,0:24:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It originated at age three in a very startling, shocking, and overwhelming way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.57,0:24:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It then reoccurred later on in different contexts during teenage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.32,0:24:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it then recurred even more severely later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.05,0:24:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the very depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And since that time, the mind really says nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.75,0:24:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinkingness can occur if it's an occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.10,0:25:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And thinkingness is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.32,0:25:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not the source of one's information.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.44,0:25:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of one's information, you know, shines forth spontaneously of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.36,0:25:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This week I was walking out to feed the chickens or something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.62,0:25:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it became shockingly obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.16,0:25:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That the self, the personal self, is reborn every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.45,0:25:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.55,0:25:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went, wowzy, wowzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.75,0:25:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wowzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.43,0:25:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.33,0:25:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't thinking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.71,0:25:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't thinking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.68,0:25:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Going out to feed the chickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.08,0:25:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.04,0:25:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And that the personal self is not continuous and linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.92,0:25:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a retrospective falsification.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.96,0:25:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.10,0:25:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.60,0:25:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.56,0:25:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.50,0:25:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.24,0:25:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.40,0:26:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And you play it all together and it looks like every instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.70,0:26:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The self is reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.49,0:26:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.25,0:26:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Recreated.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.33,0:26:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,From instant to instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.41,0:26:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're not stuck with the linearity at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.04,0:26:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The opportunity to become enlightened is...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.54,0:26:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you miss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.53,0:26:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.75,0:26:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The opportunity to become enlightened is...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.18,0:26:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the halos around everybody's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.08,0:26:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The room lit up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.18,0:26:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.95,0:26:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you prove that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.93,0:26:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.27,0:26:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.93,0:26:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it so?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.15,0:26:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.69,0:26:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you go into an infinite state, it's in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.11,0:26:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.31,0:26:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no prodroma.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.65,0:26:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't get more and more and then become the greatest, the morest.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.79,0:27:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not at all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.55,0:27:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's totally that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.20,0:27:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.84,0:27:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as soon as you turn off the movie machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.30,0:27:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Frames stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.20,0:27:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.28,0:27:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the infinite sense of self, with a capital S,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.35,0:27:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of one's own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.87,0:27:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is always continuously present.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.83,0:27:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Always continuously present.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.34,0:27:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.30,0:27:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It merely awaits the dropping of energizing the desire for experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.56,0:27:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we're addicted to experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.44,0:27:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't just the payoff of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.76,0:27:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the experiencing of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.83,0:27:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So this probe, this experiencer, with its ravenous hunger,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.11,0:27:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is always out there seeking to avoid what it senses inside as a nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.13,0:28:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks without somethingness, it'll be left with nothingness and cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.08,0:28:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it chooses to reign.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.93,0:28:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The narcissistic ego doesn't believe in God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.15,0:28:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks it is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.69,0:28:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.67,0:28:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the source of your experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.06,0:28:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And the narcissistic ego is, therefore, threatened by divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.65,0:28:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's threatened by divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.57,0:28:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.79,0:28:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll do anything to avoid divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.49,0:28:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, any reference to divinity is now illegal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.34,0:28:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we don't mention a certain name here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.74,0:28:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For fear we will offend somebody and make them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.44,0:28:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, not uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.81,0:28:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to make anybody uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.48,0:28:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, please, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.42,0:29:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you all have a duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.31,0:29:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People confuse spirituality with passivity, milksopism.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.66,0:29:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality requires courage to stand up for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.97,0:29:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you all have a duty, which I'll give you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.60,0:29:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Constitution of the United States says,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.32,0:29:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of the divinity of our source, we are all equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.76,0:29:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of the divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.08,0:29:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of the divinity of our creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.54,0:29:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the Congress not establish any religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.18,0:29:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,nor, nor prohibit the free practice thereof.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.58,0:29:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice how cleverly the second half of the sentence is never mentioned?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.03,0:29:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor prohibit the free practice thereof.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.11,0:30:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Such as putting a Christmas tree on your lawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.14,0:30:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.24,0:30:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.10,0:30:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor prohibit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.42,0:30:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor prohibit the free practice thereof.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.54,0:30:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, instead of a peace parade, I would appreciate it if you would write your congressman, your senator, Bill O'Reilly, the president, whoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.48,0:30:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to have forgotten the second part of the sentence in the United States Constitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.28,0:30:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.60,0:30:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, even those that are pro-maintaining the establishment of religious as a core essence of society,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.46,0:30:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves don't even know it, or ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.54,0:30:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.00,0:30:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you get anywhere if you don't know the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.66,0:31:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And secondly, if you don't stand up for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.56,0:31:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't win with wimpism.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.86,0:31:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wimpism.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.61,0:31:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality does not mean soppy wimpism.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.79,0:31:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Limpy, limpy wimpism.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.67,0:31:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They take me down, they're going to have to do it against my protest.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.79,0:31:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's my lecture for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.87,0:31:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is going to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.87,0:31:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, confusion of spirituality with passivity and non-action.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.46,0:31:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, non-action is an internal function.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.88,0:31:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an external action.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.13,0:31:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-action means one automatically reflects the truth to the greatest understanding of which they are capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.47,0:31:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To facilitate the development of the spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.47,0:32:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend generally contemplation rather than meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.01,0:32:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation has its place.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.69,0:32:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very intense, it's very precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.09,0:32:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's usually done in this corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.07,0:32:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,with these flowers and this incense and these bells and gongs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.76,0:32:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And now when it's over,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.96,0:32:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddamn neighbors, what the hell are they wearing the raver?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.01,0:32:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes compartmentalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.23,0:32:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it isn't who you are, it's what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.57,0:32:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand how meditation...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.93,0:32:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know zillions of people that meditate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.67,0:32:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And they really aren't much farther than they were when they started.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.84,0:32:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Including pranayama, which calibrates at 2.30.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.42,0:32:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're expecting pranayama to get you to heaven, it's going to be a slow trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.93,0:33:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.82,0:33:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So spirituality is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.90,0:33:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.88,0:33:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,With...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,With your own existence, in the here and now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.08,0:33:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinary vision focuses on the near side of an object because it intends to manipulate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.62,0:33:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A contemplative lifestyle focuses on the far side of objects because it's inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.42,0:33:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if I'm going to do something with these flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.80,0:33:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I focus on this, so I don't knock it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.50,0:33:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.88,0:33:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I'm enjoying the flowers, I get the totality of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.93,0:33:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm not going to do something with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.85,0:33:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The focus of concentrated focus is about 20 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.58,0:33:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,About 20 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.44,0:33:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In training the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.09,0:33:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Police are trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.97,0:34:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you focus on your opponent, your range is 20 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.02,0:34:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And although you see him, you miss his accomplice here, who just shot you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.02,0:34:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't see him over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.88,0:34:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So even in police work, it's recommended to have a diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.16,0:34:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.20,0:34:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you intentionally make your visual field diffuse,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.20,0:34:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you go from 20 degrees to 200 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.08,0:34:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,From 20 to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.48,0:34:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.86,0:34:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a certain way is contemplative in which you become one with the overall field.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.11,0:34:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You align with the context rather than the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.94,0:34:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you need the specifics of content to perform a function.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.13,0:34:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm going to snip off the flower,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.81,0:35:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to really focus where to have the scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.86,0:35:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But to include the beauty of the flowers in my life is total.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.63,0:35:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If they said, sit down and draw the flowers as you saw them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.67,0:35:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do that because I don't have that much linearity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.12,0:35:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Focusing on the flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.49,0:35:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So to have a contemplative way of being in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.09,0:35:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this becomes habitual.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.58,0:35:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As you do it, as you become contemplative,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.54,0:35:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as you're walking to feed the chickens,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.94,0:35:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you get the self is reborn every instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.94,0:35:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,God, it's so obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.04,0:35:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.15,0:35:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You could think a thousand lifetimes and never realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.03,0:35:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You could think 1,000 lifetimes and never realize that the self is reborn every instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.42,0:35:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.22,0:35:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.18,0:35:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.28,0:35:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You live a thousand lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.78,0:36:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and never realize that,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.13,0:36:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,well,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.02,0:36:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,why is it reborn as what it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.86,0:36:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because for karmic reasons, the movie is playing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.10,0:36:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you want to know, you want to put the next film in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.42,0:36:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Your habit is to always react this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.62,0:36:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the karmic propensity pulling you back into identification with the personal limited self.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.69,0:36:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The contemplative lifestyle tends to take you out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.69,0:36:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You tend to become, who you are tends to become more diffused.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.45,0:36:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good word, diffused.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.85,0:36:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you become more diffused all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.81,0:36:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the whole room rather than one spot in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.32,0:36:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.38,0:36:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, we've wandered from the chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.21,0:36:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.07,0:36:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,From this map of consciousness that evolved from the Gorsy Miracle students
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.66,0:37:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,who did not go weak with fluorescent lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.52,0:37:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.36,0:37:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, what's the matter with these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.90,0:37:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So if any of you have not done the course, and you're going to do the course,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.92,0:37:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be fun just to have somebody test you looking at fluorescent lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.76,0:37:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They make 100% of you a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.40,0:37:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And sweet and low various things over your solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.36,0:37:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after you get to about less than 90 or something like that, retest yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.06,0:37:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've done that with personal friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.35,0:37:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.11,0:37:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.39,0:37:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of that, we came out with a logarithmic scale of 1 to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.80,0:37:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the scale doesn't prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.42,0:37:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to re-contextualize kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.74,0:37:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology is affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.53,0:37:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you a sense of the degree of reliability, confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.31,0:38:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really a confirmatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.47,0:38:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That somebody would need.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.29,0:38:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A scale to discern severe truth from a severe falsehood seems astonishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.56,0:38:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see that a good part of the world is unable to differentiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.62,0:38:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is intrinsically classically termed evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.59,0:38:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,unable even when it's stunning them, even when it's right in their face,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.59,0:38:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,even when it's on a poster 20 feet by 40 feet, they can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.59,0:38:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That incapacity, then, of the human mind to discern truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.84,0:38:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.30,0:38:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the kinesiologic numbers are would be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.51,0:38:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what we could call level of confidence in statistics and mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.35,0:38:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We have what's called level of confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.87,0:38:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so at what level of confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.07,0:39:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We use the symbol P.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.55,0:39:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,P is less than .01, less than .001.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.32,0:39:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And the more zeros you get, the greater the confidence you can put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.46,0:39:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So that mathematical statistical system is...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.82,0:39:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,parallel, comparable to what we do with kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.28,0:39:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quicker, and so it's merely confirmatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.02,0:39:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you the level of confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.62,0:39:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say kinesiology indicates the degree of the level of confidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.78,0:39:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,actually, of spiritual truth and of reality in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.44,0:39:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is well known, and of course, because I was a psychiatrist for many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.17,0:39:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we put the emotions that go...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.01,0:39:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So with this, also the process going on in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.80,0:39:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have the law, and we have these levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.52,0:39:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the view of yourself, and the view of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.94,0:39:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.57,0:40:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And we really could...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.48,0:40:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of God, we could even have one lower than this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.28,0:40:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because if we can go lower than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.52,0:40:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there are people who literally hate God, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.92,0:40:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And any mention of God, of divinity, makes them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.84,0:40:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.72,0:40:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I haven't made anybody uncomfortable this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.83,0:40:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how narcissistic this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.26,0:40:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a problem with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.98,0:40:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that makes me uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.01,0:40:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, it makes me uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.05,0:40:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes you uncomfortable, buddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.59,0:40:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It says God over the courthouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.23,0:40:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, go around the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.78,0:40:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, 78% of the world's population lives below the level of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.10,0:40:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,See the great mass of it on this graph.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.71,0:40:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of people from 200 and up is quite limited on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.83,0:40:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.27,0:41:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at human history, when you listen to the evening news,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.39,0:41:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you can understand why.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.63,0:41:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we put it this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.69,0:41:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that people from 200 and up are small,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.43,0:41:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,numerically small, numerically small.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.88,0:41:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However, because of their relative power,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.32,0:41:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they offset.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.92,0:41:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The negativity of the 78%.
